acceptOwnership().details: The new owner accepts the ownership transfer.

bridgeBurn(uint256,uint256,bytes32,addre.details: In case of native token vault _data is the tuple of _depositAmount and _receiver.

params._assetId: the assetId of the asset being bridged
params._chainId: the chainId that the message will be sent to
params._data: the actual data specified for the function
params._msgValue: the msg.value of the L2 transaction. For now it is always 0.

returns._bridgeMintData: The calldata used by counterpart asset handler to unlock tokens for recipient.

bridgeMint(uint256,bytes32,bytes).details: Note, that while payable, this function will only receive base token on L2 chains, while L1 the provided msg.value is always 0. However, this may change in the future, so if your AssetHandler implementation relies on it, it is better to explicitly check it.

params._assetId: The assetId of the asset being bridged.
params._chainId: The chainId that the message is from.

params._nonNativeToken: The address of token on its origin chain.
params._tokenOriginChainId: The chain id of the origin token.

returns._0: Address of an L2 token counterpart.

constructor.details: this contract is deployed in the L2GenesisUpgrade, and is meant as direct deployment without a proxy.

params._aliasedOwner: The address of the governor contract.
params._bridgedTokenBeacon: The address of the L2 token beacon for legacy chains.
params._contractsDeployedAlready: Ensures beacon proxy for standard ERC20 has not been deployed.
params._l1ChainId: The L1 chain id differs between mainnet and testnets.
params._l2TokenProxyBytecodeHash: The bytecode hash of the proxy for tokens deployed by the bridge.
params._legacySharedBridge: The address of the L2 legacy shared bridge.
params._wethToken: Address of WETH on deployed chain

ensureTokenIsRegistered(address).details: This function is used to ensure that the token is registered with the NTV.

getERC20Getters(address,uint256).details: Receives and parses (name, symbol, decimals) from the token contract

params._token: The address of token of interest.

params._l1Token: The address of token on L1.

returns.expectedToken: The address of token on L2.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

pendingOwner().details: Returns the address of the pending owner.

registerToken(address).details: The goal is to allow bridging native tokens automatically, by registering them on the fly.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Starts the ownership transfer of the contract to a new account. Replaces the pending transfer if there is one. Can only be called by the current owner.

bridgeBurn(uint256,uint256,bytes32,addre.notice: Allows bridgehub to acquire mintValue for L1->L2 transactions.

bridgeMint(uint256,bytes32,bytes).notice: Used when the chain receives a transfer from another chain's Asset Router and correspondingly mints the asset.

calculateCreate2TokenAddress(uint256,add.notice: Calculates L2 wrapped token address given the currently stored beacon proxy bytecode hash and beacon address.

constructor.notice: Initializes the bridge contract for later use.

ensureTokenIsRegistered(address).notice: Ensures that the native token is registered with the NTV.

l2TokenAddress(address).notice: Calculates L2 wrapped token address corresponding to L1 token counterpart.

pause().notice: Pauses all functions marked with the `whenNotPaused` modifier.

registerToken(address).notice: Registers tokens within the NTV.Allows the bridge to register a token address for the vault.No access control is ok, since the bridging of tokens should be permissionless. This requires permissionless registration.

setLegacyTokenAssetId(address).notice: Sets the legacy token asset ID for the given L2 token address.

tokenDataOriginChainId(bytes).notice: Returns the origin chain id from the token data.

tryRegisterTokenFromBurnData(bytes,bytes.notice: Tries to register a token from the provided `_burnData` and reverts if it is not possible.

unpause().notice: Unpauses the contract, allowing all functions marked with the `whenNotPaused` modifier to be called again.
